spanGrp.span: Okay, me, I'm called Diqajata Qamayeena
aa qawasch hud gesarmanay geroon aa mulbadaw
When I was a girl I often dance the gerona and mulbadaw dances
Nilipokuwa binti nachezaga gerona na Mulabadaw
I was with Damegoda's family of Qamara
Nilikua na akina damegoda wa kwa Qamara
Okay, when I went to marry
qayaj hudumeed ab dugwmuhosht gesarmanay mulbadaw gend jeed barbayiig
I was a girl there in Dugwamuhosht and we dance the mulbadaw, we were with the Barabaig.
Nilikuwa binti huko dugwamuhoshta na tunacheza ngoma ya mulbadaw tupo ndani ya barbayiga
When I was there I came to marry
There often we danced and went to ceremonies
Kule huwa tunacheza ngoma na kwenda matambikoni
This is a thing of the Asimjeeg
ha gabiideew hosh aa do dab deebug iiyeeny
I stayed there until I had two children
Nilikaa kule hadi nilipokuwa na watoto wawili
I moved all the way to Makuyuni
heet qawuny dabigw gicha aa qawuny mang'ol
Many days later I came to return to Mang'ola
I arrived and my husband was killed
ha gend jeed asimjeeg gesinay qadowong'wak aa bacmheeng dumjeeng aa qawuy garm
We were with the Asimjeeg and went to dance and I became a woman
Tukawa ndani ya waasimjega na kwenda tu ngoma na nimekuwa mwanamke
aa qon qameew gwargweedeeny aa gabalagw aa qawuny ng'anyiin
My husband passed away and I moved to this area
Mume wangu akaja kufa na nikahamia nchi hii
qayiid gich aa gand jeed asimjeeg hiji
I came here and was then with the Asimjeeg
Nikaja huku twna nikawa kwa waasimjega
asees ab asimjeeg aa bat qadoweed gil aa bat dumjeeng
Us, the Asimjeeg, what we are continuing with is dancing and doing ceremonies
Sisi kwa waasimjeega tunachoendeleza ni kwenda ngoma na matambikoni
